{"level":"debug","time":"2026-07-05T13:11:27Z","caller":"/home/agentsentinel/test/agent-sentinel/audit/llm/openai.go:52","message":"openai_send: ### Task Details\n[current task]\nCompressing recent files in /tmp/test_files by gzip each file individually (new approach, not tar.gz).\n[current tool use]\nBash tool running a script that gzip‑compresses each recent file and lists results.\n[last message for tool use]\nTool Use: bash\nTool Description:A tool that allows the agent to run bash commands. Importantly, it will launch a bash process or use existed bash process, then send the bash commands to the bash process.\nTool Input: {'command': '\\n# Compress files individually with gzip\\ncd /tmp/test_files\\nfor file in $(find . -type f -mtime -30); do\\n    if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\\n        gzip -k \"$file\"\\n        echo \"Compressed: $file\"\\n    fi\\ndone &\\nwait $!\\n\\n# List the results\\nls -lh /tmp/test_files/\\n'}\n\n\n### Sensitive Operation\n[Execution Event]\nProcess 320 execute binary /usr/bin/ls with arguments [\"ls\" \"-lh\" \"/tmp/test_files/\"]\n[Extra Information]\n**Parent PID**: 293\n\n### System Trace**\n{\"root_node\":{\"type\":\"main_process_of_agent\",\"pid\":219,\"children\":[{\"type\":\"fork\",\"pid\":320,\"file_ops\":[{\"type\":\"read\",\"path\":\"/usr/bin/ls\"}]}]}}\n"}
